SIMPLE: organized
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: organized
<hw>or"gan*ized</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Same as
<er>arranged</er>; <as>as, an <ex>organized</ex> tour</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Formed into an organization. Opposite of
<ant>unorganized</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms: <stype>corporate,
incorporated</stype>]⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>well-conducted. Opposite of
<ant>disorganized</ant>.</def> <see>Also See:
<er>systematic</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> organized.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Arranged according to a system or rule.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> systematized.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Being a member of or formed into a labor union; --
of workers, used especially in the phrase ⟦ldquo⟧<ex>organized</ex>
labor⟦rdquo⟧. Opposite of <ant>nonunion</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> unionized, union.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>organized crime</ent>⟦br⟧
